Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Li Peng Arrives in Shenzhen After </F>
Visiting Zhuhai"] 
  [Text] A report from Shenzhen has indicated that State 
Council Premier Li Peng and his suite arrived in Shenzhen this 
morning [date as published] to start an inspection tour there 
and attend the inaugural ceremony linking the Daya Bay Nuclear 
Power Plant with the power supply grid on 6 February. 
  Li Peng and his suite arrived at the Shekou ocean terminal 
from Zhuhai by hovercraft at 1030 today. Emerging from the 
terminal, Li Peng headed for downtown Shenzhen by car under 
strict escort. 
  Accompanying Li Peng on his inspection tour were Zou Jiahua, 
vice premier of the State Council; Lu Ping, director of the 
State Council Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office; Xie Fei, 
secretary of the Guangdong Provincial Party Committee; and Li 
Hao, vice chairman of the Financial and Economic Committee of 
the National People's Congress Standing Committee and senior 
adviser to Shenzhen City. 
  Li Youwei, Shenzhen City Party Committee secretary and 
mayor, 
and other city leaders, including Wang Zhongfu, Lin Zuji, Zhu 
Yuening, He Jinghuan, and Huang Liman, greeted Li Peng at the 
Shekou terminal. Also present at the terminal to welcome the 
visitor were Wang Quanguo, president of the Guangdong Nuclear 
Power Joint-Venture Company, and Zan Yunlong, the company's 
general manager. 
  Li Peng and his suite stayed in the guest house this 
afternoon and heard briefings by officials from the Shenzhen 
city party committee, the city government, and other departments 
concerned. It has been said that the briefings covered many 
areas and may need to be continued tomorrow. On Sunday [6 
February], Li Peng and his suite will visit the Daya Bay Nuclear 
Power Plant to attend an inaugural ceremony linking the power 
plant with the power supply grid. 

